ical ideologies, encourage persisting senses of national identity, and act as barometers for the changing ideological climate of the modern and increasingly globalized contemporary world. Through rigorous scholarly analyses, the book's contributors help to illuminate the increasing significance of large-scale sporting events on the international stage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aNationalism and sportsxHistory. 0aSports and globalizationxHistory. 0aSportsxCross-cultural studiesxSociological aspects. 0aSportsxSocial aspectsvCross-cultural studies. 0aSportsxSociological aspectsvCross-cultural studies. 4aCultural Studies : Identity. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / Olympics & Paralympics.2bisacsh1 aArchetti, Eduardo P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrewster, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClaire,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, CL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdelman, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Robert S. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuttmann, Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennett, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLondon, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacAloon, John J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMason, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMessner, Michael A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRowe, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStevenson, Deborah, econtri